                            <comment id="15102181" author="chernals" created="Fri, 15 Jan 2016 17:49:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Same problem here. The insert works when the index is not present. I&apos;ve been tracking this error since last night, great that you passe by on SO.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;qlsh:kepler&amp;gt; drop table test;&lt;br/&gt;
cqlsh:kepler&amp;gt; CREATE TABLE test (k int, t int, s text static, v text, PRIMARY KEY (k, t));&lt;br/&gt;
cqlsh:kepler&amp;gt; INSERT INTO test(k, t, s, v) VALUES (0, 1, &apos;abc&apos;, &apos;def&apos;);&lt;br/&gt;
cqlsh:kepler&amp;gt; CREATE INDEX ix ON test (t);&lt;br/&gt;
cqlsh:kepler&amp;gt; INSERT INTO test(k, t, s, v) VALUES (0, 1, &apos;abc&apos;, &apos;def&apos;);&lt;br/&gt;
Traceback (most recent call last):&lt;br/&gt;
